# TypeScript & React Coding Standards

## File Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `FormHeader.tsx`, `Step1.js`)
- Pages: lowercase with extensions (e.g., `page.tsx`, `client.tsx`)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `utils.js`)

## Component Structure
Follow the existing pattern seen in [src/components/form/FormHeader.js](mdc:src/components/form/FormHeader.js):

```tsx
// Imports first
import React from 'react';
import { useTranslations } from 'next-intl';

// Component with proper TypeScript types
const ComponentName = ({ prop1, prop2 }: Props) => {
  const t = useTranslations();
  
  return (
    <div className="component-class">
      {/* JSX content */}
    </div>
  );
};

export default ComponentName;
```

## State Management
- Use Redux for global form state - see [src/store/slices/formSlice.js](mdc:src/store/slices/formSlice.js)
- Follow the established pattern for state updates
- Use local state for component-specific data

## Internationalization
- Always use `useTranslations()` hook for text content
- Reference message keys from [messages/](mdc:messages/) files
- Use descriptive translation keys that match the context

## CSS Classes
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes for styling
- Use custom SCSS classes from [src/scss/](mdc:src/scss/) for complex components
- Follow BEM methodology for custom class naming
